The paper discusses the use of conformance checking techniques to assess the suitability of a process model in representing an underlying process, observed through a collection of real executions. This involves the analysis of the relation between processes and models, which is a common topic in software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also proposes a new metric for precision based on the notion of anti-alignment, which involves the comparison of observed behavior with the behavior produced by the model. This requires the use of machine learning techniques to analyze event logs and process models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the complexity of computing anti-alignments, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the paper proposes a new metric for precision that satisfies most of the required axioms, which involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques to evaluate the quality of process models (cs.AI).
